<subSubSection id="24CB1080FFA2FFFCFAB2AA7F817AF9E7" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFA2FFFCFAB2AA7F817AF9E7" blockId="22.[151,1437,973,1539]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFAB2AA7F815EFACF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1297,1323]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of São Paulo include Ilhabela (Ilha de São Sebastião) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFF78AA7F80B5FAAB" author="Luederwaldt, H." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref67517" refString="Luederwaldt, H. (1929) Resultados de uma excursao cientifica a Ilha de Sao Sebastiao no litoral do Estado de Sao Paulo em 1925. Revista do Museu Paulista, 16, 1 - 79." type="journal article" year="1929">Luederwaldt 1929</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFA2FFFCFB67AA598138FAB6" box="[274,349,1335,1362]" degrees="24" direction="south" minutes="4" orientation="latitude" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" precision="925" value="-24.066668">24°4′S</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="09E525CCFFA2FFFCFB13AA5981ACFAB6" box="[358,457,1335,1362]" degrees="44" direction="west" minutes="24" orientation="longitude" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" precision="925" value="-44.4">44°24′W</geoCoordinate>
(MNRJ 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFFA2FFFCF85BAA5B82E0FAAB" box="[558,645,1333,1360]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.04494" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="in" value="3561.0">3561 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF8F8AA5B8322FAAB" author="Dall'Occo, P. L." box="[653,839,1333,1359]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref60273" refString="Dall'Occo, P. L. (2010) Taxonomia e Distribuicao das Lagostas (Crustacea: Decapoda: Achelata e Polychelida) no Oceano Atlantico. PhD Thesis (unpublished), Universidade Estadual Paulista (Unesp), Rio Claro, 432 pp." type="book" year="2010">Dall’Occo 2010</bibRefCitation>
). It seems there is no special commercial fishery for it, even if it is caught as bycatch throughout its range (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF883AA3783FDFA97" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[758,920,1369,1395]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
) together with 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFE36AA3484F8FA97" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1804" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1804" box="[1091,1181,1370,1395]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palinuridae" genus="Panulirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFE36AA3484F8FA97" box="[1091,1181,1370,1395]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. argus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFEDEAA37852AFA97" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1195,1359,1369,1395]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFF2EAA378170FA7C" author="Gaeta, J. C. &amp; Silva, M. B. &amp; Godoy, T. &amp; Cruz, R." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1705" refId="ref63307" refString="Gaeta, J. C., Silva, M. B., Godoy, T. &amp; Cruz, R. (2015) Update on the lobster species from Rocas Atoll Marine Reserve, Brazil. Check List, 11 (4), 1705. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 11.4.1705" type="journal article" year="2015">
Gaeta 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFAE2AA1080B5FA73" box="[151,208,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
); the yield of its fishery seems to be largest in 
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFA2FFFCF950AA13830CFA73" box="[805,873,1405,1431]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCF90CAA138479FA73" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[889,1052,1405,1431]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 292" refId="ref64998" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1991) Marine lobsters of the world. An annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of interest to fisheries known to date. FAO Fisheries Synopsis, 125 (13), 1 - 292." type="journal article" year="1991">Holthuis 1991</bibRefCitation>
) as bycatch of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFEBCAA1085F0FA73" authorityName="Giraldes &amp; Smyth" authorityYear="2016" box="[1225,1429,1406,1431]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palinuridae" genus="Panulirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meripurpuratus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFEBCAA1085F0FA73" box="[1225,1429,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. meripurpuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As well as the case of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFBE6AACC823AFA5F" authorityName="Giraldes &amp; Smyth" authorityYear="2016" box="[403,607,1442,1467]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palinuridae" genus="Panulirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meripurpuratus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFBE6AACC823AFA5F" box="[403,607,1442,1467]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. meripurpuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, episodic recruitment can explain the rare occurrences of 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA2FFFCFE9CAACC851AFA5F" box="[1257,1407,1441,1467]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palinuridae" genus="Senex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevicauda">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFE9CAACC851AFA5F" box="[1257,1407,1441,1467]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">P. laevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FFA2FFFCFAE2AAAB80BDFA3B" box="[151,216,1477,1503]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Bahía</collectingRegion>
de la 
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFA2FFFCFB69AAAB81F4FA3B" box="[284,401,1477,1503]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Ascensión</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFA2FFFCFBD5AAAB819EFA04" box="[416,507,1477,1504]" name="Mexico" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Mexico</collectingCountry>
), persistent adult populations are unlikely to occur in this region (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA2FFFCFEABAAAB8176F9E7" author="Briones-Fourzan, P. &amp; Barradas-Ortiz, C. &amp; Negrete-Soto, F. &amp; Segura-Garcia, I. &amp; Lozano-Alvarez, E." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="694 - 698" refId="ref55391" refString="Briones-Fourzan, P., Barradas-Ortiz, C., Negrete-Soto, F., Segura-Garcia, I. &amp; Lozano-Alvarez, E. (2019) Occurrence of Panulirus meripurpuratus and Panulirus laevicauda (Decapoda: Achelata: Palinuridae) in Bahia de la Ascension, Mexico. Latin American Journal of Aquatic Research, 47 (4), 694 - 698. https: // doi. org / 10.3856 / vol 47 - issue 4 - fulltext- 11" type="journal article" year="2019">
Briones-Fourzán 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA2FFFCFAE2AA8480AAF9E7" box="[151,207,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
